This is bang on. The article provides the info you need. Referencing the above chart; 

"When a device has multiple compliance policies, then the highest severity level of all the policies is assigned to that device."

Which is to say, if a device is NONCOMPLIANT WITH ANY POLICY ASSIGNED TO IT, which all 3 of these devices are, then it is NONCOMPLIANT OVERALL.
